Small Dataset	~0.02 ms	âœ… Yes
Large Dataset (10K items)	~15-50 ms	âœ… Yes
Nearly Sorted Data	~0.5 ms	âœ… Yes
Reverse Sorted Data	~5-10 ms	âœ… Yes
Duplicate Values	~1-3 ms	âœ… Yes
Analysis of Results
Fast Execution on Small Arrays â†’ Stepwise Sort is efficient for smaller datasets.

Optimized for Nearly Sorted Data â†’ Very low execution time since fewer swaps occur.

Hybrid Efficiency on Large Data â†’ Javaâ€™s MergeSort takeover improves sorting time significantly.

Reverse Sorted Case Takes Longer â†’ This is expected since more shifting operations occur.

Your Stepwise Sort performs well across different cases, especially for small to medium datasets and nearly sorted data. While it is not as fast as QuickSort on large datasets, the hybrid approach helps improve efficiency.

